summary:
The Security Council,
 Acting in accordance with Article 28 (3) of the Charter of the United Nations,
Decides to hold meetings in Nairobi from 18 to 19 November 2004, with the agenda “The Reports of the Secretary-General on the Sudan”;
Decides to discuss Sudan with representatives of the African Union and the Intergovernmental Authority on Development, and to discuss other regional peace efforts with them;
Decides to waive the requirement for verbatim records of these meetings to be made available on the first working day following the meeting, and instead to issue them in New York subsequently.
